hands_on_practices.solution:
1. Quadratic Zeeman shift in ground state:
   $$\Delta E_Q=\langle H_Q\rangle
   =\frac{e^2B^2}{8m}\langle x^2+y^2\rangle
   =\frac{e^2B^2}{8m}\,2a_0^2
   =\frac{e^2a_0^2}{4m}B^2.$$
2. Fine‐structure splitting for n=2:
   $$E_{2,j}^{\text{(FS)}}
   =-\frac{R_y}{4}\frac{\alpha^2}{4}\Bigl(\frac{2}{j+\tfrac12}-\tfrac34\Bigr).$$
   For j=3/2: factor=(1−3/4)=1/4 ⇒ $E_{2,3/2}=-R_y\alpha^2/64$.
   For j=1/2: factor=(2−3/4)=5/4 ⇒ $E_{2,1/2}=-5R_y\alpha^2/64$.
   $$\Delta E_{\text{FS}}
   =E_{2,3/2}-E_{2,1/2}
   =\frac{4R_yα^2}{64}
   =\frac{R_yα^2}{16}.$$
3. Set equal:
   $$\frac{e^2a_0^2}{4m}B^2=\frac{R_yα^2}{16}
   \;\Rightarrow\;
   B^2=\frac{mR_yα^2}{4e^2a_0^2}.$$
4. Substitute 
   $$R_y=\tfrac12m c^2α^2,\quad a_0=\frac{\hbar}{m cα},\quad 
     e\hbar=2m\mu_B.$$
   Then
   $$B^2=\frac{m\,(½m c^2α^2)α^2}{4e^2\,(\hbar^2/(m^2c^2α^2))}
           =\frac{m^4c^4α^6}{8e^2\hbar^2}
           =\frac{m^4c^4α^6}{8(2m\mu_B)^2}
           =\frac{m^2c^4α^6}{32m^2\mu_B^2}
           =\frac{c^4α^6}{32\mu_B^2}.$$
   Taking the square root:
   $$B=\frac{mc^2α^3}{4\sqrt2\,\mu_B}.$$
5. Final expression:
   $$B=\frac{m c^2\,α^3}{4\sqrt2\,\mu_B}.$$
